description:
DLLs for referencing from VisualStudio integration projects.
			Make sure you follow the rules for referencing DLLs from specific VS versions. The referenced DLL must be legitimate in context of the VS-version-affinity of your project.
			A JustVsXY.dll can only be referenced from the same-version JustVsXY project. It MUST NOT be used in any SinceVsUV project, because it's only available in one specific VS version.
			A SinceVsXY.dll can be referenced from JustVsUV or SinceVsUV, provided that XY is not above UV.
			AnyVs.dll is actually SinceVsXY where XY is below any supported VS, so it can be used freely.
summary: DLLs for referencing from VisualStudio integration projects.
title: JetBrains Platform VisualStudio Reference DLLs for AnyVs, Redist Private Build of Select DLLs
